# Architecture Rules

## Naming

- Use clear English file and folder names for code and configuration.
- Keep generated artifacts separate from source files when possible.
- Prefer stable names over temporary labels.

## Structure

- Store global conventions in `CLAUDE.md/global.md`.
- Store repository-specific decisions in `CLAUDE.md/project.md`.
- Store repeatable workflows in `skills/`.
- Store automation hooks in `hooks/`.
- Store delegated roles in `subagents/`.
- Store packaging and team distribution files in `plugins/`.

## Engineering Guardrails

- Avoid broad refactors unless the task specifically calls for them.
- Prefer existing libraries and project patterns.
- Add comments only when they clarify non-obvious behavior.
- Verify changes with targeted checks before calling work complete.

